I completely understand your concern and sincerely apologise for the inconvenience caused. I just wanted to suggest a quick call so I can guide you step by step on how we can go about this.
From what I can see, you also have another booking for 39 weeks that you processed yourself. Even we make bookings directly through IQ‚Äôs main website, and since your move-in date is so close, the availability keeps changing quite dynamically. Rooms often get sold out quickly, and at times they appear available again if another student cancels. You can also check with the property team on this.
Since the 43-week contract was already signed, it would be difficult for the property to issue a refund. However, what we can do here is request IQ to transfer the deposit from the 43-week contract to your 39-week booking. This way, when you move ahead with the 39-week contract, you won‚Äôt need to pay the deposit again.

The cancellation request would need to come directly from you as the student, but we‚Äôll be there to support you throughout. Had this not been a misunderstanding, we would have been more than happy to help you book the 39-week contract from the start. Since you are our valued client, we want to make this process as smooth as possible for you.
If this works for you, we‚Äôll draft an email to the property team requesting the deposit transfer and ensure you are copied in for complete transparency. Please let me know if you‚Äôd like us to proceed this way. :)

Speaker A: Hello? Hello, you may speak with Biancu.
Speaker B: Yes, speaking.
Speaker A: Yeah, hi, this is Shikha from Amber Student. This call is regarding your accommodation. You are searching in London.
Speaker B: Yes.
Speaker A: Yeah. So you just told me that you are looking for only for 39 weeks.
Speaker B: Yes, I'm looking for something for 39 weeks. Yes.
Speaker A: Yeah. So we have this property available, IQ Arcade, which is a copper room. 39 weeks from 13th of September. And it will cost you 277 pound per week. And I can see that only four rooms are left for the 39 weeks. So you can proceed ahead with this one. It will be. All the bills will be included. Your utility bills.
Speaker B: Would it be possible to send me the on email or a Link on. On WhatsApp so I can have a look at it because my son needs to see it as well.
Speaker A: Okay, could you please confirm your son full name?
Speaker B: Confirm a what?
Speaker A: Your son full name.
Speaker B: It's Victor. Victor Ovidenia. V I C P O R V I V T O R. Okay, yes. Ovidania O V I OVI D E D E N I E N I E yes, all right.
Speaker A: Yeah, I have texted you on a WhatsApp. You can just have a look, okay.
Speaker B: And just bear with me. I need to go downstairs, I want to ask something. I went on to the Amber website and there is a phone number on the website to which I called but it comes up at potential fraud.
Speaker A: So on which number have you tried calling me?
Speaker B: Right, so there is a number here ending in 1634. Just a second ending with 1634.
Speaker A: I don't know which number are you talking about? If you can just like refer me the same and the screenshot which you are getting while calling the number, we can have a look into that.
Speaker B: It says powered by Amber. So that's why I'm confused because I'm not sure who I am talking at the moment because obviously we.
Speaker A: No, no, no, I. No, no.
Speaker B: About you know, paying quite large amounts of money and I'm not really confident that I am.
Speaker A: No, no, don't worry about that. We are like partner. Yes, yes, we are partner with the UCLA college itself, University College London. And we got your details from there itself to help you out with your accommodation.
Speaker B: Okay.
Speaker A: Yeah.
Speaker B: Right, so let me have a look on WhatsApp then. Just bear with me. Sure. So this is the copper room iq the arcade.
Speaker A: Let me just see the availability again. Sorry, yeah, I'm just checking the availability for the 39 weeks because the availability keep on changing every time.
Speaker B: Okay, can I just ask before I go and speak to him. Can I ask what are the terms for payment?
Speaker A: So this property offers four installment payment plans. One will be due in the month of this August 2nd will be due in the month of like October or November 3rd would be in the January 4th would be in the April 2026. So four installment payment plan, you can get it.
Speaker B: Okay, so the total of the room would be like 10,803 pounds. And this is divided by four installments. So 2,700 per installment. Okay.
Speaker A: Approximately.
Speaker B: And this is with everything. So we don't have to pay anything else on top of that for the. All bills are included.
Speaker A: All. Yeah.
Speaker B: Okay.
